11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 1731, as
13 amended by Section 1, Chapter 176, O.S.L. 2024 (21 O.S. Supp. 2024,
14 Section 1731), is amended to read as follows:
15 Section 1731. A. Larceny of merchandise held for sale in
16 retail or wholesale establishments shall be punishable as follows:
17 1. For the first or second conviction, in the event the value
18 of the goods, edible meat, or other corporeal property which has
19 been taken is less than One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), the person
20 shall be guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by imprisonment in the
21 county jail for a term not exceeding thirty (30) days, and by a fine
22 not less than Ten Dollars ($10.00) nor more than Five Hundred
23 Dollars ($500.00); provided, for the first or second conviction, in
24 the event more than one item of goods, edible meat, or other
